Vice President Mike Pence spoke from FEMA Headquarters in Washington, D.C. about the federal government's support for the state and local efforts in Houston. He expressed the President's thoughts and prayers and emphasized the commitment to providing assistance for rescue and recovery. Pence commended the cooperation between FEMA, state officials, and local governments. He assured that the federal government has the reserves to address the financial burden of the crisis, and Congress is expected to provide additional resources if needed. Pence urged Texans to heed the direction of local emergency management and stay safe. He confirmed that President Trump will be visiting Texas and that the administration will continue to provide support and prayers for the people of Houston.